Idea is to recursively explore all valid combinations.
    There are 2 options in every step.

1. Open: if there are more paranthesis to open. if there is an open paranthesis, there must be a close paranthesis too. So increment closable by 1.
1. Cose: recursively do this iff there are any closable paranthesis left.

```

class Solution {

    private List<String> res = new ArrayList<>();

    public List<String> generateParenthesis(int n) {
         rec(n,0,"");
        return res;
    }

    void rec(int rem, int closable, String cur){

        if(rem==0 && closable==0){
            res.add(cur);
            return;
        }

        if(rem>0)
            rec(rem-1, closable+1, cur+"(");

        if(closable>0)
            rec(rem,closable-1,cur+")");
    }
}
```

