## Explanation:

### Solution 01

- Using ***Valley Peak Approach.***
- As we need maximum profit so we can compare prices between 2 days!
- If the next day price is greater than the current day, we'll buy it and sell it the next day!
- **Time complexity:** O(n).

### Solution 02

- Same as 1, but here we’ll store previous value in ***mn***.
- **Time complexity:** O(n).

---

## Code:

```cpp
//Solution 01:
class Solution {
public:
    int maxProfit(vector<int>& prices) {
        int n= prices.size(), profit=0;
        for(int i=1; i<n; i++){
            if(prices[i]>prices[i-1])
                profit += prices[i]-prices[i-1];
        }
        return profit;
    }
};

//Solution 02: 
class Solution {
public:
    int maxProfit(vector<int>& prices) {
        int n=prices.size(), profit=0;
        int mn=prices[0];

        for(int i=1; i<n; i++){
            if(mn<prices[i]){
                profit += prices[i]-mn;
            }
            mn = prices[i];
        }
        return profit;
    }
};
```

