solutions.content:
This approach involves solving subproblems from length 1 to length n. Here we represent subproblem as dp(i) which indicates maximum profit made till ith day. 
Results for subproblem is based on following recurrence.

`dp(i) = dp(i-1) + price(i) - price(i-1)`
`dp(0) = 0,  zero profit for first day (this is a base case)`
```
class Solution {
    public int maxProfit(int[] prices) {
        int n = prices.length;
        int[] dp = new int[n];
        dp[0]=0;
        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
            dp[i] = dp[i-1] + Math.max(0,prices[i]-prices[i-1]);
        }
        return dp[n-1];
    }
}
```

