solutions.content:
Given an integer array prices where prices[i] is the price of a given stock on the ith day.
On each day, decide to buy and/or sell the stock and one can only hold at most one share of the stock at any time. However, buy it then immediately sell it on the same day.
Find and return the maximum profit achieve.
**Example:**
						Input: prices = [7,1,5,3,6,4]
						Output: 7
**Explanation**: 
							Buy on day 2 (price = 1) and sell on day 3 (price = 5), profit = 5-1 = 4.
							Then buy on day 4 (price = 3) and sell on day 5 (price = 6), profit = 6-3 = 3.
							Total profit is 4 + 3 = 7.

# **Java Solution:**
Runtime: 0 ms, faster than 100.00% of Java online submissions for Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock II.
Memory Usage: 42.1 MB, less than 96.76% of Java online submissions for Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock II.
```
class Solution {
    public int maxProfit(int[] prices) {
        // Initialize the max profit...
        int maximumProfit = 0;
        // Traverse all the element through loop...
        for(int i=1; i<prices.length; i++) {
            // Set the difference so that we can get the max profit...
            int diff = prices[i]-prices[i-1];
            // If the difference is positive value, add to profit and increse it...
            if(diff > 0){
                maximumProfit += diff;
            }
        }
        return maximumProfit;      // Return the max profit...
    }
}
```

