I have seen a lot of solutions finding the best subarray, but the problem really boils down to wether the price is increasing or decreasing day over day. For example, if the prices are ```[1, 2, 3, 4, 5]```. Solving for the max profit by buying on Day 1 at $1 and selling on Day 5 at $5 for a profit of $4 is the same as buying and selling every day ($2-$1 + $3 - $2 + $4 - $3 + $5 -$4). For cases when the price goes down, there is no reason to track the price as it will either increase on the next iteration (in which case it will be added) or it will continue going down. Hope this helps!

