# TL;DR;

Key here is you can buy and sell the stock at same day. only constraint is you can only hold 1 stock at a time. so you sell it when profit and buy it same again and sell it if tomorrow price is higher, the profit just cummulates

# Details

Take the example [8, 2, 5, 6, 3, 10, 1]

Try to plot it in a paper as a graph
it looks like 

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/610aecf9-fe3b-4d47-a41c-01982b353ae2_1635116844.8589506.png)

Now the problem becomes very easy
you just buy when you see low point and sell at high point
But you may think: what if today is low (but you still get profit as the amout you got is lesser than todays market value) but tomorrow may be really high, should i hold onto the stock? 
Yes you can --> but the problem becomes very hard now that you have to know the values ahead and keep a state. 
instead --> you sell today, get a profit and store the profit, and then buy the stock back again, and hold the new one and sell it off tomorrow, again when the market is higher. 

this is emulated in the code where i just sell and then rebuy. but in a code way where i just get the difference. 

lets take an example: 

i got a stock brought at Rs 1 (got yesterday -- say)
today value is Rs 5 ( if i sell today the profit is 4) but tomorrow the market is at 10
if i just hold on and sell the Rs 1 stock at 10 --> my profit is 9

but you still get same profit if  you sell today at 5 (profit 4) then rebuy same stock at 5 and sell tomorrow at 10 (profit 5) so total profit is (4+5) still 9

