> we can decide 1st transaction as buy on prices[lo] and sell on prices[hi]
> the 2nd transaction may start at day hi + 1 or latter
> assume we know max profit from day hi + 1 (to prices.length - 1)
> `max profit from day i, state[i] = max(prices[hi] - prices[lo] + state[hi + 1])`
> we define `maxProfitFrom(start)` to represent `state[i]` and enumerate `lo, hi`
> we add memorization to avoid duplicate calls on maxProfitFrom
