# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Buying and selling stock may feel like a complicated question, but when you break it down, the rules are very simple.

This problem boils down to buying stock at the local minima, and selling stock at the local maxima.

![extremaPoints.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/e6610c4d-a07e-41de-8272-ab70fb517d59_1677716743.8909247.png)
(Taken from google)

Logically, this makes sense, as you are buying when the stock is lowest and selling when the stock is highest.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
The implementation for this is very simple. For every point in time,
1. If you are buying, check if the price ahead in time is greater. If it is, buy.
2. If you are selling, check if the price ahead in time is lower. If it is, sell.

The algorithm only has 3 variables. The total profit, the price that you are buying at, and a boolean whether you are buying or not.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int maxProfit(vector<int>& prices) {
        int profit = 0;
        int buyPrice = 0;
        bool buying=true;

        for (int i = 0; i < prices.size()-1; i++)
        {
            if (buying)
            {
                // If at local minima, buy stock
                if (prices[i+1]>prices[i]) { 
                    buying = false;
                    buyPrice = prices[i];
                }
            }
            else {
                // If at local maxima, sell stock
                if (prices[i+1]<prices[i]) {
                    buying = true;
                    profit += prices[i]-buyPrice;
                }
            }
        }

        // Edge case for selling stock
        if (!buying && prices[prices.size()-2]<=prices[prices.size()-1]) profit += prices[prices.size()-1]-buyPrice; 

        return profit;
    }
};
```

