solutions.content:
On observing a complete binary tree, we notice that it fulfills one of the following cases:
```
Case 1: Tree is a full binary tree with all leaves at last level
        1
      /   \
     2     3
    / \   / \
   4   5 6   7       count =  2^(level+1)-1

Case 2: Left subtree is full
        1
      /   \
     2     3
    / \   / 
   4   5 6           count = size of root(1) + left full tree + recurse in right subtree

Case 3: Right subtree is full
        1
      /   \
     2     3
    / \   / \
   4   5 6   7
  / \
 8   9                count = size of root(1) + right full tree + recurse in left subtree
```

That will form the main function. Now, the question comes down to how to identify if a complete binary tree is full? Simple. Look at the depths of the tree through the leftmost nodes vs. rightmost nodes. If left depth == right depth, you have a full binary tree.

Here's the code:
```
class Solution {
    public int countNodes(TreeNode root) {
        if (root==null) return 0;
        int ld = leftDepth(root);
        int rd = rightDepth(root);
        if (ld==rd) // full tree
            return (int)Math.pow(2, ld+1)-1;
        int lrd = rightDepth(root.left);
        if (lrd==ld-1) {// left subtree is full
            return (int)Math.pow(2, ld) + countNodes(root.right);
        } else {// right subtree is full
            return (int)Math.pow(2, rd) + countNodes(root.left);
        }
    }

    private int leftDepth(TreeNode root) {
        if (root==null) return 0;
        int d = 0;
        while (root.left!=null) {
            root=root.left;
            d++;
        }
        return d;
    }

    private int rightDepth(TreeNode root) {
        if (root==null) return 0;
        int d = 0;
        while (root.right!=null) {
            root=root.right;
            d++;
        }
        return d;
    }
}
```
Edit: Using the optimizations mentioned by [@aarvee](https://leetcode.com/aarvee) , we can modify the recursive calls to avoid repeated call to leftDepth or rightDepth. The new function becomes:
```
public int countNodes(TreeNode root) {
	return countNodes(root, -1, -1);
}

private int countNodes(TreeNode root, int leftDepth, int rightDepth) {
	if (root==null) return 0;
	// calculate depths only if not already available
	int ld = leftDepth == -1 ? leftDepth(root) : leftDepth;
	int rd = rightDepth == -1 ? rightDepth(root) : rightDepth;
	if (ld==rd) // full tree
		return (int)Math.pow(2, ld+1)-1;
	int lrd = rightDepth(root.left);
	if (lrd==ld-1) {//left subtree is full
		return (int)Math.pow(2, ld) + countNodes(root.right, -1, rd-1);
	} else {// right subtree is full
		return (int)Math.pow(2, rd) + countNodes(root.left, ld-1, -1);
	}
}
```

