solutions.content:
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/sunnymeow/image_1550736413.png)
1. get the height of left and right subtree
2. compare the height
	- if left == right, then the left subtree must be complete
	- if left > right, then the right subtree must be complete
	- if a subtree is complete, the number of whole subtree + the root = 2^subtree height
3. recursion

```
class Solution {
    public int countNodes(TreeNode root) {
        if (root == null) {
            return 0;
        }

        int leftHeight = getHeight(root.left);
        int rightHeight = getHeight(root.right);

        // left tree is complete
        if (leftHeight == rightHeight) {
            return (1 << leftHeight) + countNodes(root.right);
        } 
        // right tree is complete
        return (1 << rightHeight) + countNodes(root.left); 
    }

    public int getHeight(TreeNode root) {
        if (root == null) {
            return 0;
        }    
        return 1 + Math.max(getHeight(root.left), getHeight(root.right));
    }
}
```

